<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter    
45</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>  
My heart is inditing a good matter: I speak of the things which I have made     
touching the king: my tongue is the pen of a ready writer.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>Thou art fairer than the children   
of men: grace is poured into thy lips: therefore ELOHIYM hath blessed thee for  
ever.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>Gird thy 
sword upon thy thigh, O most mighty, with thy glory and thy majesty.</P></TD>   
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>And in thy majesty     
ride prosperously because of truth and meekness and righteousness; and thy      
right hand shall teach thee terrible things.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A 
NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>Thine arrows are sharp in the heart of the king's 
enemies; whereby the people fall under thee.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A 
NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>Thy throne, O ELOHIYM, is for ever and ever: the  
sceptre of thy kingdom is a right sceptre.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A   
NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>Thou lovest righteousness, and hatest wickedness: 
therefore ELOHIYM, thy ELOHIYM, hath anointed thee with the oil of gladness     
above thy fellows.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>All thy garments smell of myrrh, and aloes, and cassia, out of the ivory 
palaces, whereby they have made thee glad.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A   
NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>Kings' daughters were among thy honourable women: 
upon thy right hand did stand the queen in gold of Ophir.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD  
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>Hearken, O daughter, and          
consider, and incline thine ear; forget also thine own people, and thy father's 
house;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>So    
shall the king greatly desire thy beauty: for he is thy ADOWN; and worship thou 
him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>And the 
daughter of Tyre shall be there with a gift; even the rich among the people     
shall intreat thy favour.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>      
13</H4></TD><TD><P>The king's daughter is all glorious within: her clothing is  
of wrought gold.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>She shall be brought unto the king in raiment of needlework: the virgins 
her companions that follow her shall be brought unto thee.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>With gladness and rejoicing shall 
they be brought: they shall enter into the king's palace.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD  
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>Instead of thy fathers shall be   
thy children, whom thou mayest make princes in all the earth.</P></TD></TR><TR> 
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>I will make thy name to be    
remembered in all generations: therefore shall the people praise thee for ever  
and ever.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software is copyright 2000 by John M.   
